I didn't catch the original question, but I did see that
don@security.ov.com (Donald T. Davis) wrote:

>see "how to explain zero-knowledge protocols to your children,"
>by quisquater, guillou, and berson, crypto '89 proceedings, springer.

Also see Mike Fellows and Neil Koblitz, "Kid Krypto," in the Crypto '92 
proceedings at p. 371ff. Koblitz has an ongoing interest in teaching 
significant mathematical concepts to children. He is in the math department at 
U. Washington in Seattle. Contact him.

Best,
--Tom Berson
